ance of the 1930s and 1940s. Originally published in 1983, this edition brings back into print a highly regarded work of dance history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Dance / Classical & Ballet.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999z978311071360240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822396567zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822396567423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822396567.jpg  a978-3-11-071360-2  DUK Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999c1964d1999  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles